article.headline: Fairfield 53, Siena 52
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Greg Nero led a balanced Fairfield attack with 10 points and eight rebounds and the Stags limited Siena to 34.6 percent shooting from the floor to post a 53-52 win in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference play Tuesday night. The Stags (5-9, 3-1 MAAC) limited the Saints (8-6, 3-1) to their second lowest point total in the Fran McCaffery era. "Obviously, this game was a struggle for us all night," McCaffery said. "I thought we battled and competed, especially in the second half, and certainly had our opportunities." Neither team scored in the final 1:44 after Ryan Rossiter's tip-in for Siena closed the gap to 53-52. The Saints forced two Fairfield turnovers in the final 18 seconds. Siena's Edwin Ubiles scored 11 of his 15 points in the second half to lead all scorers. He shot 7-15 from the floor while the rest of the team combined to shoot just 11-38. The Stags took the lead for good on Anthony Johnson's tip-in with 10:26 left in the first half. Siena played without leading rebounder Alex Franklin and junior forward Josh Duell. Leading scorer Kenny Hasbrouck played through foul trouble and finished with just three points. Rossiter had 11 points and nine rebounds.
